{"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/TimeValProtocol"]]},"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"toIso8601","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"() -> "},{"text":"String","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:SS"},{"text":"!","kind":"text"}],"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"anchor":"discussion","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"ISO 8601 allows a large number of date\/time formats, with or without"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"punctuation and optional elements. The format returned by this function","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"is a complete date and time, with optional punctuation included, the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"UTC time zone represented as “Z”, and the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"tv_usec"},{"text":" part included if","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"and only if it is nonzero, i.e. either"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"“YYYY-MM-DDTHH:MM:SSZ” or “YYYY-MM-DDTHH:MM:SS.fffffZ”."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"This corresponds to the Internet date\/time format defined by","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/www.ietf.org\/rfc\/rfc3339.txt"},{"text":",","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"and to either of the two most-precise formats defined by","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the W3C Note","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"http:\/\/www.w3.org\/TR\/NOTE-datetime-19980827"},{"text":".","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Both of these documents are profiles of ISO 8601."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Use "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_date_time_format()"},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_strdup_printf()"},{"type":"text","text":" if a different"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"variation of ISO 8601 format is required.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"If ","type":"text"},{"code":"time","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" represents a date which is too large to fit into a ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"struct tm"},{"type":"text","text":","},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"nil","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" will be returned. This is platform dependent. Note also that since"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GTimeVal"},{"text":" stores the number of seconds as a ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"glong"},{"text":", on 32-bit systems it","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"is subject to the year 2038 problem. Accordingly, since GLib 2.62, this"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"function has been deprecated. Equivalent functionality is available using:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","code":["GDateTime *dt = g_date_time_new_from_unix_utc (time_val);","iso8601_string = g_date_time_format_iso8601 (dt);","g_date_time_unref (dt);"],"syntax":null},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The return value of "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_time_val_to_iso8601()"},{"type":"text","text":" has been nullable since GLib"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"2.54; before then, GLib would crash under the same conditions."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"to_iso8601 is deprecated:"}]},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"#GTimeVal is not year-2038-safe. Use"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"g_date_time_format_iso8601(dt) instead."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"kind":"content"}],"kind":"symbol","sections":[],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/TimeValProtocol\/toIso8601()","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Converts "},{"code":"time","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" into an RFC 3339 encoded string, relative to the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Coordinated Universal Time (UTC). This is one of the many formats"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"allowed by ISO 8601."}],"metadata":{"symbolKind":"method","role":"symbol","externalID":"s:4GLib15TimeValProtocolPAAE9toIso8601SSSgyF","modules":[{"name":"GLib"}],"platforms":[],"title":"toIso8601()","extendedModule":"GLib","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"toIso8601"},{"text":"() -> ","kind":"text"},{"text":"String","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:SS"},{"text":"!","kind":"text"}],"roleHeading":"Instance Method"},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/timevalprotocol\/toiso8601()"]}],"references":{"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/TimeValProtocol":{"role":"symbol","type":"topic","fragments":[{"text":"protocol","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"TimeValProtocol"}],"kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Represents a precise time, with seconds and microseconds."}],"navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"TimeValProtocol"}],"url":"\/documentation\/glib\/timevalprotocol","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/TimeValProtocol","title":"TimeValProtocol"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/TimeValProtocol/toIso8601()":{"url":"\/documentation\/glib\/timevalprotocol\/toiso8601()","role":"symbol","type":"topic","deprecated":true,"title":"toIso8601()","abstract":[{"text":"Converts ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"time"},{"type":"text","text":" into an RFC 3339 encoded string, relative to the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"Coordinated Universal Time (UTC). This is one of the many formats","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"allowed by ISO 8601."}],"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"toIso8601","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"() -> "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:SS","text":"String"},{"kind":"text","text":"!"}],"kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/TimeValProtocol\/toIso8601()"},"http://www.w3.org/TR/NOTE-datetime-19980827":{"title":"Date and Time Formats","url":"http:\/\/www.w3.org\/TR\/NOTE-datetime-19980827","titleInlineContent":[{"text":"Date and Time Formats","type":"text"}],"type":"link","identifier":"http:\/\/www.w3.org\/TR\/NOTE-datetime-19980827"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib":{"abstract":[],"kind":"symbol","title":"GLib","role":"collection","url":"\/documentation\/glib","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib","type":"topic"},"https://www.ietf.org/rfc/rfc3339.txt":{"title":"RFC 3339","url":"https:\/\/www.ietf.org\/rfc\/rfc3339.txt","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"RFC 3339"}],"identifier":"https:\/\/www.ietf.org\/rfc\/rfc3339.txt","type":"link"}}}